<h1>Your Deccan Queen on Rails tickets are confirmed</h1>
<p>Hello <%= @order.buyer_name %>,</p>
<% if @documents_pending %>
  <p>Payment for order <strong><%= @order.code %></strong> is confirmed. Your tax invoice is being prepared and will be available from your order page.</p>
<% else %>
  <p>Payment for order <strong><%= @order.code %></strong> is confirmed. Your tax invoice is attached.</p>
<% end %>
<p>You’ve got <%= pluralize(@order.tickets.count, "ticket") %> — <%= link_to "assign them to your attendees here", order_url(@order.code) %>.</p>

<p>You can also send an attendee their own private link. They fill in their name, dietary needs, T-shirt size and childcare, and their ticket is emailed straight to them:</p>

<ul>
  <% @order.tickets.reject(&:canceled_at?).each do |ticket| %>
    <li>
      <%= ticket.ticket_type.name %> —
      <% if ticket.assigned? %>
        <%= ticket.attendee_name %> (<%= link_to "update details", ticket_claim_url(ticket.claim_token) %>)
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to "claim this ticket", ticket_claim_url(ticket.claim_token) %>
      <% end %>
    </li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

<p>Keep this email — these links are how you and your attendees manage the tickets.</p>
<p>See you in Pune.</p>
